HEADWORD: Rowport
<hw>Row"port</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>An
opening in the side of small vessels of war, near the surface of the
water, to facilitate rowing in calm weather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

